The paper discusses security and verification of software execution on remote embedded devices, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The focus on safety-critical systems and low-end embedded devices suggests a potential fit for systems and control (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of sensors and actuators also suggests a potential fit for embedded systems (cs.ET).
